HOUSE BILL 500
Q4 6lr1416
HB 357/25 – W&M CF SB 309
By: Delegates Hartman, Anderson, Arentz, Baker, Buckel, Chisholm, Ciliberti,
Fisher, Griffith, Hornberger, Jacobs, Kipke, R. Long, Miller, T. Morgan,
Nkongolo, Reilly, Tomlinson, and Valentine
Introduced and read first time: January 27, 2026
Assigned to: Ways and Means
Committee Report: Favorable with amendments
House action: Adopted
Read second time: March 23, 2026
CHAPTER ______
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Sales and Use Tax – Precious Metal Bullion or Coins – Exemption
3 FOR the purpose of altering the definition of “precious metal bullion or coins” for purposes
4 of eligibility for an exemption from the sales and use tax for the sale of precious metal
5 bullion or coins; expanding the exemption by repealing requirements a requirement
6 that the sale price exceed a certain amount and the sale occur at the Baltimore
7 Convention Center; and generally relating to a sales and use tax exemption for
8 precious metal bullion and coins.
9 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
10 Article – Tax – General
11 Section 11–214.1
12 Annotated Code of Maryland
13 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
14 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
15 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
16 Article – Tax – General
17 11–214.1.
18 (a) In this section:
EXPLANATION: CAPITALS INDICATE MATTER ADDED TO EXISTING LAW.
[Brackets] indicate matter deleted from existing law.
Underlining indicates amendments to bill.
Strike out indicates matter stricken from the bill by amendment or deleted from the law by
amendment. *hb0500*

2 HOUSE BILL 500
1 (1) “precious metal bullion or coins” means:
2 (i) any precious metal that has gone through a refining process and
3 is in a state or condition such that its value PRIMARILY depends on its precious metal
4 content and not on its form; or
5 (ii) except as provided in paragraph (2) of this subsection, monetized
6 bullion, coins, or other forms of money that:
7 1. are manufactured from precious metals; and
8 2. are or have in the past been used as a medium of exchange
9 under the laws of the State, the United States, or a foreign nation; and
10 (2) “precious metal bullion or coins” does not include jewelry or a work of
11 art made of precious metal bullion or coins.
12 (b) The sales and use tax does not apply to a sale of precious metal bullion or coins
13 [if:
14 (1) the sale price is greater than $1,000; and
15 (2) the sale occurs at the Baltimore Convention Center].
16 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
17 1, 2026.
Approved:
